/*  --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    tweenMachine.mel - MEL Script
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
  
    DESCRIPTION:
  	Creates a new key inbetween the previous and next keys, using a
  	slider to adjust the "bias" or weight that each key has over the
  	new key.  Requested/inspired by Doron Meir.  :)
  
    USAGE:
  	source tweenMachine; tweenMachine;
  
    AUTHOR:
  	Justin S Barrett - http://www.justinsbarrett.com
  
    ADDITIONAL CREDITS:
  	xml_lib.mel: J. Adrian Herbez
  
    COPYRIGHT:
  	Copyright 2005-2014 Justin Barrett  - All Rights Reserved
  
    VERSIONS:
    2.00 - Initial release of upgrade
    2.01 - fixed issue with "Add Groups" UI display
         - fixed timeline tick display issue
         - disabled auto-refresh when opening a scene
         - added support for character sets
    2.02 - removed need to source file before running
         - added support for special tick color (v7 and higher)
    2.03 - updated tick color support for Maya 200X versions
    2.04 - bug fix related to character set support
    2.05 - fix issue that prevented group and set dialogs from working in newer
           versions of Maya
         - fix bug that cropped off sliders and buttons for user defined sets
           in newer versions of Maya
    2.0.6 - Fixed a bug where selecting attributes in the channel box would not
            find the proper animCurve nodes for tweening
          - Changed the version numbering scheme
          - Moved sourcing of xml_lib out of base procedure
    2.0.7 - After tweening, focus is now set to the main Maya window instead of
            the last active panel.
    2.0.8 - Improved selected channel parsing to handle missing node/attribute
            combinations, and attributes with no connected curves
            
*/

